-- GM U.S. December sales down 9.6 pct
-- 
-- Wed Jan 3, 2007 7:01pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/04/us-gm-sales-idUSWEN171220070104

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - General Motors Corp. on Wednesday said its U.S. December sales fell 9.6 percent from a year earlier, driven by a decline in truck sales. 

 The world's largest automaker sold 341,327 vehicles in the United States last month, compared with 392,041 vehicles a year earlier.